,Recommended,221260,13655213,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,jmomo,"Somewhere uncomfortably wedged in between hilarious and deeply disturbing is this game.What will you do the first time you light a bus full of school children on fire, hearing their screams before it explodes?Will you laugh?Will it shock you?Will it scare you?Or will you glare mindlessly into the warm orange abyss, and feel nothing at all?Is this game about the dangers of over-consumption and runaway-consumerism, leading to a post-apocalyptic society where children are asked to burn their toys in a desperate attempt to stay warm to survive?Is this game about corporate and government wrongdoing, having milked an entire society dry of all it's resources until the CEOs and top officials flee the planet, leaving the glazed-eyed slack-jawed starving populace to their fate of an eternal nuclear winter?Is this game a metaphor for the player's wasted life? Like your character who burns all of his toys in the fireplace, is the player burning his life away playing video games, staring into the warm glow of his computer monitor while the real world behind him goes unnoticed, unlived?Is there any escape offered by burning down your house, the prison that keeps you inside, or is it even worse out there in the unknown?Playing this game won't give you any answers, but it will let you ask the question."
,Recommended,221260,1700658,"Posted: 9 September, 2013",all,ChrisG,"This game seems to be a reference to our throwaway society.You start with a catalog of items which you can buy and burn in your fireplace, they will delivered to you in time from 5 seconds to 2+ minutes. They cost virtual money and you can earn money for burning them. The whole game contains 7 catalogs à 20 items which you have to unlock by burn more and create combination. (Sushi + Pufferfish)Combinations can create funny effects in your fireplace. Between your burning fun you will get letters from your neighbor and other people. This is meant as story and is kinda interesting if you interprete it correct.As further you go as crazier the items will be. Burn the universe!!!The end has really surprised me cause %§3rR0R&&/%SPOIL%""ERrQR%&$§Nice entertainment for cold days. 7/10"
,Recommended,221260,18529336,"Posted: 17 October, 2015",all,Artibius,"PROS:+ nice feel & ending of the story+ relaxing gameplay+ awesome visual effects+ morbid humor+ ideal game for pyromaniacsCONS:- not much replayability- slightly repetitive item burning- a couple of item combinations do not really fit their namesComment:""What is this game???"" ... that is what I asked myself multiple times when playing. At first it seemed like the game is just one of those free desktop destroying apps - a nice way to relax but without any real substance. But while minimalistic there is a story, which I found really sweet and cool. Each combo is a name, which must be analyzed as to what items it could contain. While trying some combos got repetitive and there is not much replayability I can for sure recommend this game to anyone wishing to relax (no achievement or point hunting here!). Also a must have to all the pyromaniacs out there!------------------------------------------------------------------If you liked this review you can find more on theCurator pageor in myReview Corner."
