,Recommended,221260,26193265,"Posted: 23 October, 2016",all,Junie,"Wow, where do I start!?I'm writing this review on 10/23/2016. A friend of mine giftend me this almost a year ago,I loved it then and I love it just as much now. I think I may love it even MORE now than I did, now that I""ve had tine to sit on it.There are two very important things that I pay attention to when I try games. The art and the music; because I'm a very emotional person and I find that those are the two aspects that really get me into a game.Little Inferno BLOWS it ALL out of the water.The art is just phenominal. It's smooth, unique, and makes me feel very comfortable. I'm not sure how that will relate to anyone else, but everything just feels so smooth. Each item has its own personality. The game controls and mechanics are very comfortable, very natural. You left click to drag and drop. Very simple. The graphics are unique and the goals are challenging as hell! You really, REALLY have to think very hard when it comes to some of the goals within the game.The music is SO very emotional... I think the music is a good 70% of the game. The dialogue is 20% and the rest is the gameplay itself. I've downloaded the music for my own personal collection because I love it so much. It is definitely someting that helped drive me through the game.The game is simple, try to match up the combos. But pay attention to the story line that SHE gave you. LIsten to her very carefully, it's very important. Listen.... pay attention! ..... what did we talk about???"
