,Recommended,221260,8633182,"Posted: 9 January, 2014",all,SoggyWarmPockets,"Having played and beat World of Goo, I kind of thought I knew what I was in for with this game. I was wrong. Just like World of Goo, the developers have taken amazingly addictive gameplay in which you throw toys and expired food into a fireplace and burn them to get money and stamps to order more; and threaded an intriguing story into it, almost imperceptibly. They force you to think, not just about what items to burn together to unlock combos, but about why you are doing what you are doing. This game is witty, engaging, satirical, and haunting in a way that creeps up on you. Absolutely brilliant."
