76561198198241997,Recommended,221260,28716186,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,laser,the game is great theres a great story to the game its fun to burn things and the song it great ITS LITTLE INFERNO ITS LITTLE INFERNO JUST FOR ME
,Recommended,221260,925536,"Posted: 17 March, 2013",all,7grain,"To paraphrase Hyperbole and a Half: ""Burn ALL the things!""Little Inferno is a curious way to waste a few hours. You have a fireplace. You order toys and other objects from catalogs not to play with, but to burn. Sometimes, the mailman brings letters from the neighbors. You'll burn those, too.It's a little bit creepy and, yes, entertaining. Is there more to this game? Yes. No. Both, I think.Fans of Kyle Gabler's earlier work, ""World of Goo"", will recognize a similar smug poke at the things we take for granted in this always-online age, but I don't mean to suggest that there is somehow more of a game here than ""burning stuff."" Suffice to say that there are varying levels of interaction going on with the things you burn. I don't think that's a spoiler. It's game enough that there is a beginning, a middle, and an end.However, the artistic style and soundtrack are the true star of this game. My daughter walked in on me playing, and within 10 seconds she asked ""Is that a new game from World of Goo?"" Gabler's artwork and music are immediately recognizable.Just as in ""World of Goo"", the art of Little Inferno defines a warm and unsettling world, where a fun game with simple mechanics is just the exposed surface of a much larger world gone awry. Or... not! These games can be played by a 5-year-old, but jaded adults will naturally seek deeper meaning."
76561198124475910,Recommended,221260,10464469,"Posted: 13 June, 2014",all,SoulScream,"Very relaxing, stressless and surprising game.10/10 would burn again"
,Recommended,221260,15718862,"Posted: 6 May, 2015",all,Aaron,"Little Inferno is a very unique Indie game created by Tomorrow Corperation. The nonsensical, comical game style makes the game highly enjoyable and addictive. The objective of the game is to burn various items in your fireplace in return for coins, with which you buy more items to burn! When you burn certain items together you will unlock combos, these give you extra coins and when you get ebough you are able to purchase a new catalogue containing new items to burn!When put like that the game does not sound very enjoyable, however the way in which the items react just makes you want to see more of the game.Tomorrow Corp also add in another couple of characters who you get to meet and develope relationships with as the game progresses including an annoying but lovable neighbour who circums to a tregedy later on in the game.The game play is very responsive and you do not need a good computer to run the game. The colourful design gives the game a very positive atmosphere, which seems to be uncommon in newer games.The only down critisism that I have for this game is that it does not take a long time to complete, if you do not focus on unlocking all of the combos you could complete the game in little over 2 hours. But, if you wish to piece together all of the clues than you would have to spend a lot more time on the game.To conclude:Little Inferno if a brilliant and unique game, it includes a lot of fun puzzles to solve and will keep someone entertained for a number of hours. It's relaxed game style means you are able to play it without having to stay and ""finish this bit"" as it saves the game as you go.Graphics: 8/10 Fun but still detailed and high qualityFun: 9/10  You can spend alot of time on this simple game and not get boredOveral: 6.5/10 Superb game but it is a little short for my liking.I would recommend this game to all people, exept children who are easily distressed/upset."
