,Recommended,221260,13710398,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Yuki 雪,"The gameplay focusses on burning objects and buying new ones. There are waiting times for items, which can go up to 5 minutes. Luckily, you can skip those if you have some cards you obtain from finding combos, or sometimes at random. You have an infinite supply of money. This is because the items you burn drop MAGICAL golden coins, more than you bought the item with. There's a deep message I won't spoil, but pay attention to the story well. The lighting is beautiful and fairy-tale like. The objects you can burn often have special effects. (Such as popcorn) The only downside I see to this is that people might get bored of the repetetive gameplay, which is kinda part of the game. If you don't find it appealing to burn items over and over for hours, don't buy it. If you would like that, or just are a pyromaniac, buy it post-haste. I rate this an 8.5/10"
