76561198009316076,Recommended,221260,9967866,"Posted: 28 April, 2014",all,The Matlock,"This game gets a slight recommendation, and here's why.It's not your typical game. It's one of those ""games as art"" type of things. The whole concept of the game is you order stuff from a catalog, and set it on fire. Poof! You get coins to order new things, and stamps to get them to you faster. But it's the subtext that's interesting. Your burning things like toys at first, but then you start burning, TVs, radios, e-mail, etc, almost as if you're burning away everything in your life. Get me?And there's also an environmental message in here because the game keeps talking about smoky skies and how it's been snowing for as long as anyone can remember. Hmm.....wonder what that could be, eh?It's not worth $9.99, not at all. It's interesting but it only took me 4-5 hours over the course of two days to beat it. Get it on sale if you must try it out, and you should, because it's a unique game. But don't expect a deep challenge or extraordinary gameplay. This is about as simple as it gets."
