,Recommended,221260,9911351,"Posted: 23 April, 2014",all,Nawrusi,"It`s Little Inferno just for me!This game is a really relaxing one, and it is a ton of fun to play. The most interesting aspect of this game is poperly the story, which you can analyze (or in some cases overanalyze) to have a really deep meaning, but I will get back to that.The gamepaly is really simple you have to burn stuff. And that`s the game, you do nothing more than burning stuff, and it sounds really boring but the game has a fun way, to twist this, so it becomes fun to play.Throughout the game, you will unlock more and more stuff to burn, and all the items have some unic way of burning away, this gives some fun events and senarios, which is enjorable in every way.The other part of the game, is finding combinations. To make the combinations you have to burn specifick things together, in order to unlock the secret. Normally you only get one sentence to geuse, what the combination is, and it is really fun to try to solve the code.Now to the story, the story centers around you, that have got the ""Little Inferno intertaining fireplace"" which is a toy for children in the games world. You are intreduced to four charecters in the game, and then there is the main charecter, which we get no relation to. We get to know miss Nancy, the creator of the Little Inferno, The weather man, who tells you the weather report, your upstairs neighbor Sugar Plumps, who tells you secrests and gives you tasks, and then there is the mailman, who we only meet towards the end. There are two more charecters in the game, but they are not as important for the story as the before mentiont.The analyzing part of this game, is that the fireplace could be a metaphor for gaming.Everytime the fireplace is mentiont the charecters keep taliknig about how you are just wasting time playing the game, not even in a bad way, but more in a revelatory way, where you can think about what you are doing. Sugar Plumps is also good to back of this theory, since she is talking about you two are so close, and yet so far, in relation to the fact that you are palying games together, but in the very end, you are only two screens looking at eachother, insteed of meeting in real life.If you would like a game, where you burn stuff in order to get money to burn more stuff, this is the game for you.If you are a person that like a simple stoyline you easily can interpretent on, this is a game for you.If you like to solve puzzeles, and get rewards in games, this is a game for you.I give this game a thumps up. 7 out of 10"
