,Recommended,221260,16438020,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,DemonHighwayman,"It's a simple game, the videos on the store page will give you a good idea of what the gameplay is like - burn things in a fireplace. Expanding a little on that, the idea is that you burn stuff you buy from the games store in combinations which lets you get access to another level of things to burn. And you don't have to worry about running out of in game money to buy stuff from the store as everything you burn gives you money !Some of the stuff you can burn in your little inferno are really fun, some of the stand outs for me are the mini planets, the cold heart, the nuke, the chainsaw and the valkyrie woman among others.My one gripe is there are no options, running at 1000fps isn't really nessesary so a v-sync option would be nice. And the worst for me is no volume control, the inferno itself is rather quiet as you'd expect from a fireplace but when you go to the store to buy supplies the store music is too loud and repetetive this annoys everyone in my house, myself included!Those are just small complaints though, the game has a humerous and endearing story, fun gameplay and doesn't seem to have any technical faults unlike many other games being sold these days, beware though that for me it only lasted 7.5 hours until completion (I did have to cheat a bit looking up combo's to burn though)."
