,Recommended,221260,16445084,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Kynji,"What's not to like about this game? You burn things. Things that scream.There's a mystery here to be uncovered. Why are you sitting in front of your fireplace burning all your toys? Why are some of the catalog items you burn disturbingly...wrong? What's that strange thumping coming from the other side of the wall? You have to play to find out.Little Inferno is set in front of a fireplace. You order items from catalogues, and you burn them. There are combos of items, and it's up to you to puzzle out what they are, and burn the correct combinations, in order to progress. That's all. There's nothing more. If you need more, then I suggest you move along to another game. But if you're just the least bit tempted, pull up a chair next to the fire, and burn some things with me. It's warm here, next to the fire...."
