,Recommended,221260,17165764,"Posted: 21 July, 2015",all,DuckiDeva,"I was pleasantly surprised by the actual depth of the story line, in what appeared to be a simple physics and fire puzzle type game.  The music is great, the atmosphere is spooky and single focused, and you develop attachments to characters you never even see.  The mechanism is simple, but the message is complex.All in all, I'm pleased that I bought the game, I enjoyed playing it, and forsee me buying it for friends in the future, because what's the point of having friends if you can't enable their inner pyromaniac, I ask you?  That said; I'm not sure the game has a tremendous amount of replay-ability, if you get all/most of the combos the first time through, because I don't think the emotional ""punch"" will be there if you know what's coming.This is a beautifully done game, both visually and storytelling, and well worth the price."
