,Recommended,221260,4374206,"Posted: 15 July, 2013",all,Nth RooCH,"This is just... just one of those things. To literally describe this game, it sounds like abject♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ You get money, you buy things, you burn things, and by burning things, you get money. Where's the hook? Well, there's a very, very subtle storyline, much of which I feel the player has to decide for themselves. A subtle, dark malaise, which hides in the shadows of the gameplay experience. The above description is accurate, all you're going to do is burn stuff over and over, and even if I tell you that different things burn differently and some explode or give random effects, the real hook of this game is that as you do, you're very slowly given hints as to some tragedy in the background. To me, that's almost more compelling than the pure gameplay itself. But, for those who don't give a ♥♥♥♥, there's plenty to do in finding combos from a list by burning objects together.In short, it's cheap, it's quick, it's addictive, and for those who care? It can be a surprisingly deep experience."
