,Not Recommended,221260,16556568,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,Ksempac,"Ok, i really don't get all the praises this game get.You're burning stuff in the fireplace...some find it relaxing, i just find it boring. I like playing with fire, but i don't get that vibe out of Little Inferno, since it's mostly about waiting for new items to arrive, then they burn in a few seconds. Yet, I would write that down as personal preferences, and move on.But after that, it keeps getting worse. The wait timer become higher and higher, the money you need keep getting higher. So there is even less burning and a lot more waiting than before. Even at the end of the games, you will not get to do that much of a fire because ""express delivery coupons"" are so damn rare.I at least expected some kind of payoff when you ""finished"" the game, something that would raise it past the boring waiting mechanic...Well there is an ending...and it was almost as boring as the rest.Big disappointment. I wouldn't even recommend it on sale, whatever the price, it's not worth it."
