,Not Recommended,221260,13706538,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,Dravvad,"Incredibly. Disappointing. I did NOT finish the game, nor will I ever bother with it again. Do NOT waste your money (although apparently that is the stupid, ironic point of the game?).I really do not understand people in today's society who swarm over things with cheeky, hidden messages, as if they are some sort of saving grace for something that is terrible. You know, create some horribly bad game or TV show, but if it has a ""fancy"" meaning between-the-lines, then it is suddenly the best thing ever.This game is not a game. I played it first and foremost because the photos and videos looked like it would be a funny little way to spend some time, mixing the toys and things together to do silly things, like the moon's gravity, or trying to buy enough blocks to make a little castle and then burn it down or drop something on it.And it was enjoyable in that way for a little while. But once the game started drastically delaying all of the toys when you bought them, I became very bored and annoyed very quickly. Taking away some time for me sitting with the game idle and chatting with a friend, I probably played the game less than 90 minutes. Apparently the average players go to like 5 hours to finish the game, because they have to finish burning items in these combos and so on?And once they finish the game, as I looked into it after I shut it off and decided not to go further, they're basically given a message (although I could see parts of it showing up already, after-the-fact) that they are wasting their time doing some stupid repetitive mess like playing iOS/Android games that are just collecting some dumb items and making coins.Okay... Except 1) This isn't really that game market; and 2) I realized the game was stupid, so I didn't even get near that point nor does it apply. So basically I wasted money on a game that looked really silly and fun, but only was fun for less than an hour. Everyone somewhat raves about the game, which made me feel safer in making the purchase, and often I'm skeptical about user judgment... and would have been right to be so here.People praise this game saying that it breaks out of its mold and is great with its message of ""dreams"" and ""living life."" Some people even compare it to games like Spec Ops (saying how Spec Ops is a dark and anti-fun shooting game). Now, I loved Spec Ops (I played it on Xbox first) and agree it's dark and has a great story, but I don't understand people claiming this game to fit with that. This game is nowhere near the same thing. Spec Ops has a general message about life and war, and so does many books, movies, documentaries, etc. It's not exactly a ""new"" message. If people think it is, that is mostly because they're young and simply don't understand life or the repercussions of things like war. Blowing people up in games is fun if you disconnect your mind from it, and it is easier in something like Halo. But in ""real"" war scenarios, it is harder.Anyway, I am off-track talking about Spec Ops somewhat, but the point is that this game is just a waste to take your money, but not in the same way as those dumb mobile games. There really isn't a saving grace here to be found. There is no good ""message"" or point."
