,Recommended,221260,8474055,"Posted: 31 December, 2013",all,"Where's the leak, ma'am?","Little Inferno is honestly one of my favorite games of all time. It is revolutionary and compelling, with a thought-provoking story. Having just finished the storyline, I'm going back for more. Without giving away any spoilers, I was moved by the emotional and extremely eye-opening moral of the game. Its characters were all special in there own way, putting their own twist on the story. Having purchased quite a few games during the recent Steam sale, I found the majority of them to be fun, but lacking in storyline. Little Inferno is just the opposite, putting player in close-to tear-jerking, edge of the chair positions. The developers are able to do this using astonishing music and well thought out letters from the people you are able to interact with. These letters can put you in a state of excitement, wonder, or even sadness as you worry for your companions. In conclusion, I thoroughly enjoyed this game and think that everyone should play it. It is the sun in a snow storm."
