76561198078225088,Recommended,221260,12123784,"Posted: 16 September, 2014",all,benovere,"Over-all, this is a decent game.The gameplay is rather simple. You buy stuff with in game currency, you burn said stuff, and get money from burning it to buy more stuff. Each item, however, will react differently to the flame. There is a plot involved, but that's not where the game shines.The game's biggest selling point is the creativity with each item. Many items have special effects when burned, and some will interact with each other.However, there is a major drawback to this game: it has absolutely no replayability factor. Once you've beaten the game, once you've unlocked all of the items, and once you've accomplished all of the combos (or get bored of trying to figure them out), you're likely done with this game forever. There isn't any modding support to add new items, they don't come out with new item packs every now and then, and watching the same things burn over and over again, no matter how creative they are, gets tiring.Again, overall this is a decent game. However, it is a game you will only play once or twice."
