,Recommended,221260,16738974,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,[PunLife],"Little Inferno is yet another stylish creation by Tomorrow Corporation, the creators of World of Goo (which is a fantastic game in my opinion).Just like World of Goo, Little Inferno has a very peculiar art style, which despite its oddness is rather aluring. The game revolves around the player burning different objects in a fireplace in order to both entertain himself as well as warm the house up. Lovely prospect don't you think? The objects that the player gets to burn are fairly varied, with more getting unlocked as the player earns money and completes special combinations. The combinations are simply 2 or more objects that have to be burnt at the same time. The game is fairly addictive, up to a point in which you realise that you're laughing while burning a school bus full of screaming children. Yup. That's when I realised that this game helped me develop a secret fixation with burning school buses.In all seriousness though, this game is a great time consumer and actually does make the player question their sanity at times, as well as the consequences of their actions in game. I definitely recommend it as its both enjoyable and excellent at relieving stress accumulated on a bad day."
