,Recommended,221260,16493936,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,friendly pyromaniac,"The main premise is to entertain and give pyromaniacs a safer hobby, so to speak, plus, the end is absolutely beautiful, I mean, sure, the game is short & some things are hard to combo, that just adds another interesting puzzle to the game, which, as you have stated, this game apparently is, rather than a nice little burn-everything-in-sight (SPOILER, quite literally at the end) game, that has the same incompletely-revealed story as the last game ""world of goo"" that this team made, plus, you obviously don't know how much it takes to develop a game, let alone this kind of game, the current price $9.99 is actually quite cheap for this digital burn-fest. I'm sorry if I seem offensive, but you really havn't put alot of time into this game, it would seem. You probably didn't even play after the game was beaten, which, sure, there are other things to life than just video games and, as is said in the game: ""If you've got everything you ever dreamed about, dream bigger."" which is a really nice way to leave the player, plus, the end leaves you with such a feeling of adventure, even though you probably won't be able to see what our little hero is going to do after the plot of this amazing game ends, your imagination can still run wild with what they can do, now that they know that thereis more to life than just a fireplace and some fire, some letters and some cash, which makes the experience of this game all the more worth-while, as it is quite obvious that this game is almost poking fun at how, we as gamers, sometimes tend to start to think that while they are playing a game, there is nothing to life but you, a controller and the game. So next time you want to run your mouth off at this game for things that actually make this game all the more complelling and fun, (like waiting for more toys to arrive in the mail (which actually happens in the real world, unlike most games, where you can pull a giant rocket launcher out of nowhere and still have a good amount of ammo for it, while being able to run around faster than most other people) which most people would be farmiliar with from their childhoods, checking the mail everyday, waiting excitedly for your toy to arrive, which is very present in this game) you should think about what would happen if everything happend instantly, which would result in boredom much faster, as you would have everything you want just like that, which would remove any meaning from the process of getting everything ready for when you make a huge fire that sometimes feels like you could burn your house down. Remember this next time you play this game, you might notice something that adds charm to the game, or you could just miss it because you are over-exaggerating about how long it takes to deliver something when you have plenty of instant-mailing stamps right there in your inventory."
