76561198077429566,Recommended,221260,18396621,"Posted: 9 October, 2015",all,Chickenbowser,"A fun game that acts as a commentary on free-to-play micro transaction based games. The atmosphere of the game is a strange combination of warm contentment mixed with horror and bleak abysmal fatalism that works perfectly together to create a very unique experience.Gameplay is simple; you burn things in your fireplace, you get money to buy more things, which in turn you burn in the fire. There's something delightful and glee inducing about waiting for your new item to arrive (via old fashioned snall mail) for you to immediatly toss it in the fire and watch it cease to be in new different ways. You can also build combos by burning certain items together for extra incentives.I won't discuss story because it's something that's best discovered and pieced together by the player so they can form their own opinions.Do yourself a favor and buy this game right now."
