,Recommended,221260,16786848,"Posted: 29 June, 2015",all,Matthijs,"The logic in this game is flawless: buy stuff, burn it, end up with more money than you started with. Rinse and repeat.But seriously, if you've got a few hours to kill: play this one. It will warm your heart (and your hearth, which was kind of the point). Although the gameplay is a bit monotonous, it's interesting to see what different items or combinations of items do when they burn. The story is kept a bit vague (it's cold outside and you must keep warm by burning stuff, that's all you know), but the way it is told makes you want to continue playing to find out what's actually happening.In order to find out you'll burn countless teddy bears, pirates, ninjas, mini nukes and half the solar system, because I'm not going to tell you.The only downside to this game is that it doesn't really have much replay value. After you finish it, all that's left to do is to sit in front of your fireplace and burn stuff."
