76561198043293002,Recommended,221260,16391594,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,Freeman,"Many of these reviews revolve around the game's commentary. Yes, there is a refreshing commentary on vidya and how we use it, but let's explore some other aspects of the game;The narrative is good. The story isn't spectacular, but it's good. Takes about 3 hours to work your way through it.The execution of the narrative, however, is astounding. Beautifully constructed and emotionally gripping, perfectly compensating for the raw story's imperfections. Everything from the soundtrack to the use of the fireplace as a story-explorative platform worked perfectly.Also, it's fun. It's just plain fun. The whole process of buying and burning stuff is just simply enjoyable.There's a freeplay mode if you like it that much.Lastly, the puzzle-aspect - the finding combinations - is great fun and embellishes the sandbox with some much-needed direction. More items and puzzles would be a great step forward, providing a fun sandbox with a bit more direction, but in its current state, any buyers will absolutely be getting their money's worth.In conclusion, buy the game. At the time of review, it's about 2 dollars. You won't regret this."
