76561198041381178,Recommended,221260,16005032,"Posted: 25 May, 2015",all,SamiSqaure,"I purchased this game about 3 years ago, around the time the Yogscast played it on one of their Christmas videos. Back then, I got sucked into playing it for 3 hours straight... oops.Even after completing it within a considerably short period of time, I still come back to play it. I find that personally I enjoy this kind of game much more when I'm feeling down or just need something casual and laid back to play. It's not an overwhelming first person shooter with all kinds of customizables. No. Its a fun little puzzle game.When I bought this back in December of 2012. I had just gone through surgery and just wanted a game to play. It was uncomfortable to play the typical action packed games I'm often playing, so this was a nice change. Running off medication, the game somehow seemed even weirder than it should have been! That said, It was super easy to pick up on the gameplay mechanics and I had a lot of fun trying to mix and match all the catalog items.The story was zany yet maintained a cheerful and cutesy vibe for the most part. It has the ability to be innocent enough while still creeping you out on occasion. If you're a completeionist, you'll probably spend most of your time trying to figure out all the different combos you can make! Be advised, you'll need a bit of patience with this game!With that said, I really enjoyed this indie game and would highly recommend it.So, hey. Get you're very own Little Inferno Entertainment Fireplace today!!~"
