,Recommended,221260,7976788,"Posted: 8 December, 2013",all,Riiakhan,"It's a fun little game set in a dystopian future where the world is growing ever colder and so a company is selling fireplaces and a variety of items for you to buy and burn. It's a simple puzzle game where you place objects in the fireplace and lit them up and try to create combo's from the different reactions the toys have to fire and destruction.You start with some coins which always gradually increase as you burn more and more and as you burn newer things and complete combo's you unlock more pages of items you can order and burn.Along with this is an eerie storyline told through mail from your neighbour and others along with other little details about the world. The futility of the world growing colder and you and everyone's desperate attempts at trying to heat yourselves up is chilling.So yeah, atmosphere is great. Gameplay is simplistic but fun and unique. The storyline is light but through its storytelling it doesn't need a heavy narrative.Only problem I have with the game is that some of the combo's don't make a whole lot of a sense and forced me to use a wiki to cheat. Other than that I love this gem."
