76561198018998652,Recommended,221260,3212544,"Posted: 20 January, 2013",all,Kenny,Little Inferno is a good little game what does not cost alot all u do burn stuff and go though the game i have fished Little Inferno My review is 8/10 This a fun game Enjoy
76561198039619705,Recommended,221260,4600788,"Posted: 30 August, 2013",all,AngelofNoMercyX,"This is a very unique game that was a joy to play through. I wasn't sure what to expect when I bought it, but I do enjoy burning things so I went for it. What I found was a clever little game centered around burning things in a fireplace while receiving messages from the outside world. There is a steady progression as you burn things in combos to unlock more catalogues with more things to burn, and there is an engaging story happening at the same time via letters you receive. There are goals you can achieve such as unlocking all the combos, earning stars on all the catalogues and reaching the end of the story. However, I spent a lot of time just burning things. Most of the objects have animations that are activated when they are set on fire. Here's a tip - burn the edge of the object rather than just setting fire to the middle so you don't miss out on the clever animations. For example, there is a boat that will simply explode if you burn the middle. If you burn an outer edge, you get to watch it spurt oil and then fire before blowing up. The burning is great - oil paintings melt, fragile things are quickly reduced to ash, metal things leave charred skeletons. The only feature I would have liked to have seen would be a way to make up your own combos and share them with others. If you're looking for something different that you can enjoy at a leisurely pace, this game is an excellent choice."
,Recommended,221260,4854154,"Posted: 4 January, 2013",all,Game Psych,"Yes, it seems juvenile but once you get past the title screen the game grabs you and doesn't let you go. It has a great artistic look and it appeals to everyone's desire to burn things. Wrap that up with a good moral at the end and its a good little game. The unlockable alternate ending is a nice challenge."
