,Recommended,221260,1215103,"Posted: 4 January, 2013",all,Sharia Coke,"Little Inferno is one of the most unique games I've played in years. It's relaxing and charming in a way text can not properly describe. It's important to note that the gameplay in Little Inferno has no failure state. This is not a challenging game. It's meant to be a fun distraction with fantastic music. If you keep playing to the end you will be amazed when the game suddenly becomes something very different.If you have a Wii U or are planning to get a Wii U in the near future, buy Little Inferno there. It is a superior experience on that system (which is where I first played it). If not, Steam is a perfectly fine option. Little Inferno is one of my top 10 games of 2012 and that should say a lot considering how much I play. I loved every moment of it, and I hope more of you will give it a shot."
