,Recommended,221260,10845828,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,harveybrtn,"Little Inferno is a game about setting fire to different objects. That's all there is to it...Except it's not. Little Inferno is indeed a game about setting fire to things but a game that simplistic also pulls of something unique. This game is very emotional. It makes you happy and joyful that you have fun and nobody gets hurt, it makes you feel guilty when some objects cry and scream, it makes you sad along the way of the story and most of all it makes you question what you're doing with your life. IF YOU READ ON CERTAIN PARTS OF LITTLE INFERNO MAY BE SPOILED. SPOILER ALERT. Throughout Little Inferno I've had a blast. Only when Sugar Plumps (a background character) seemingly died in a house fire did I first question what I was doing and realise some of it seemed wrong. Later in the story you see Sugar Plumps never died in the fire, she escaped and has lived free for years and years, whilst you've spent your entire life sitting behind your Little Inferno Entertainment Fireplace burning stuff. It makes you feel things and question things. THE SPOILERS HAVE STOPPED NOW. Never have I ever played a game this simplistic, yet this emotional. Little Inferno is an amazing and emotional game. I'd absolutely recommend this game although it is highly addictive and may seem like you are like the protagonist of Little Inferno.SPOILER NOTE THEORY THING: I think the Tomorrow Corporation were trying to tell us something with Little Inferno. They were telling us we shouldn't stay in on our devices etc. We should go out and live. That is truly unique. Thank you."
