,Not Recommended,221260,10547273,"Posted: 19 June, 2014",all,Yume,"I didn't dislike Little Inferno, but I do feel that it was way too expensive for the length and theme of the game. About 98% of the game is just burning things, a task that I found to be a waste of time since what generally draws me to games are good plots and well developed characters. I got the game because I was told that its storyline was really good, but it's less of a storyline and more of an ironic message you get at the end. Certainly, I can see how Little Inferno could be fun, but for those expecting an engaging plot or characters, this is not the right game. If you enjoy puzzle games or games that don't focus on story, you may like Little Inferno. I enjoyed receiving messages from my neighbor and finding combos was occasionally amusing, but overall it seemed to me that the majority of this short game was just fluff to fill the time. While that is kind of the point, that doesn't do anything to justify the cost and time spent up."
