,Recommended,221260,11365687,"Posted: 22 July, 2014",all,Brandon,"Little Inferno, in three words: Fun, Simple, Anti-ClimaticWithout ruining the story for too many people-Little Inferno is a game, about burning objects. That's it! That is to say: it's not a point that can be counted against it.So many games fail to balance story, with gameplay elements. In my experience- Little Inferno leans just a little bit more towards the 'story' aspect; but that is only true because the gameplay lacks variety, save for the objects in which you burn.What I liked:> Burning things! It's simple, and fun to play with.> The overall story arc, and the not-so-deep meaning to the game.What I disliked:> Lack of variety when it came to objects, a lot of objects were either an upgraded version of a previous object- or a 'mix and match' of effects.Little Inferno is a basic set-things-on-fire sandbox, for the pyromaniac in all of us. If you're willing to spend the money: you too could own your very own, special, spectacular, Little Inferno Entertainment Fireplace.Just don't expect it to have much replay value. I've played it twice, and I'm likely not going to hazard a third time."
