,Recommended,221260,24620875,"Posted: 30 July, 2016",all,floaterjr,"RecommendationRecommendedBase Game ScoreA+StylePuzzle/StoryRecommendation SummaryLittle Inferno is a puzzle game with a charming story. The concept is that you are simply sitting in front of a fireplace and you burn things, and you also receive letters from various characters. You complete achievements (which is how the puzzle part of the game fits in) to progress through the story. The characters themselves suprisingly have some good depth from just reading their short letters, and you will likely take a liking to them. The story itself has some nice (not to preachy) morals and a good plot, and the ending is simply great. Little Inferno is highly recommended."
