,Recommended,221260,26294983,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,metalgod88,"Little Inferno was a game I played off an on for a few years and very much enjoyed. The story is quite interesting and kept me going to find out what new items I could unlock next and ultimately ask the question, why am I burning things in my chimney and why aren't my parents stopping me?+If you're a pyro, this game is for you.+If you enjoy making things explode, this game is for you.+If you enjoy collecting coins and using those coins to buy new things, this game is for you.- My ownly dislike is the cool down time on the later items in the game. Once you buy one, you have to wait X amount of time. The more expensive it is, the longer you have to wait to buy it again. This is annoying when you are trying to figure out a specific combination of items to explode together.Aside from that, its a pretty fun game and I recommend it."
76561197989129610,Recommended,221260,26290064,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,Megabyte [RSSD],"Little Inferno is a fun little title, but not so much because of the gameplay itself as the style and humor that keeps it interesting. You will literally spend almost all of the game in two screens doing three things, but that time will accompany you with cats that fill the fireplace with poop, snake in a cans where the joke is that it’s not snakes, but hypodermic needles, extermination toys that will set fire to things you haven't managed yet, nuclear bombs, the moon, and god knows what else. The real secret to how fun this game is is the sheer variety and dark humor in the toys you will burn and watching the results. There is just enough here to enjoy to the fullest and be done about the time you finish the game itself.If you are looking for something easy, funny, and relaxing to play for a night or two after work or school, this game can certainly fit the bill depending on your sense of humor. But if you are looking for something with deep gameplay and skill-based mechanics, you are barking up the wrong tree here… the only skill this game might help you develop is word-play.You can read the full review athttp://redsectorshutdown.blogspot.com/2016/10/little-inferno-pc-review.html"
