76561197980429671,Recommended,221260,20498362,"Posted: 12 January, 2016",all,Bubba Jones,"This is a single-dimensional game about starting fires with no depth and I admit - I spent too much time playing.The gameplay exists in a small sandbox where you put things you want to burn, then you set them on fire and watch what happens.  The watch what happens part is where all the amusement is.  There are combos and some of the items synergize as they start burning together in an amusing spectacle of fire, noise, and motion.  Progress is linear, you burn stuff until you get access to new collections of things to burn until you get to the last collection of things to burn and finally figure out the combo to end the game.I spent so much time facinated by the spectacle of watching fire I forgot how simple and bland the game is.  Still, I thought it was worth my money, it may be worth yours in a sale."
